        <mxCell id="sC2nh2z6wBofH9oqhz0A-45" parent="1" style="text;html=1;whiteSpace=wrap;strokeColor=none;fillColor=none;align=center;verticalAlign=middle;rounded=0;fontFamily=Times New Roman;" value="&lt;font style=&quot;font-size: 26px;&quot;&gt;&lt;b style=&quot;&quot;&gt;`V`&lt;/b&gt;&lt;/font&gt;" vertex="1">
          <mxGeometry height="28.5" width="26" x="641" y="636.38" as="geometry" />
        </mxCell>
        <mxCell id="bss0nQ0miUn62sMUiTcV-1" parent="1" style="text;html=1;whiteSpace=wrap;strokeColor=#FF22AE;fillColor=none;align=left;verticalAlign=middle;rounded=0;spacing=5;strokeWidth=2;spacingTop=0;spacingBottom=0;" value="&lt;div&gt;&lt;font style=&quot;font-size: 13px;&quot;&gt;&lt;span style=&quot;background-color: transparent; color: light-dark(rgb(0, 0, 0), rgb(255, 255, 255));&quot;&gt;In&amp;nbsp;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;b style=&quot;background-color: transparent; color: light-dark(rgb(0, 0, 0), rgb(255, 255, 255));&quot;&gt;GQA&amp;nbsp;&lt;/b&gt;&lt;span style=&quot;background-color: transparent; color: light-dark(rgb(0, 0, 0), rgb(255, 255, 255));&quot;&gt;the&lt;/span&gt;&lt;span style=&quot;background-color: transparent; color: light-dark(rgb(0, 0, 0), rgb(255, 255, 255));&quot;&gt;&amp;nbsp;`K` and `V` heads are the same size, and they have fewer heads than the `Q`. This saves memory,&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/font&gt;&lt;/div&gt;&lt;font style=&quot;font-size: 13px;&quot;&gt;&lt;div&gt;&lt;font style=&quot;&quot;&gt;&lt;br&gt;&lt;/font&gt;&lt;/div&gt;In this &lt;b&gt;example&lt;/b&gt;, we have a &lt;b&gt;o&lt;/b&gt;&lt;b style=&quot;&quot;&gt;ne GQA group/heads&lt;/b&gt;.&lt;/font&gt;&lt;div&gt;&lt;div&gt;&lt;ul&gt;&lt;li&gt;&lt;b style=&quot;background-color: transparent; color: light-dark(rgb(0, 0, 0), rgb(255, 255, 255));&quot;&gt;&lt;font style=&quot;font-size: 13px;&quot;&gt;&lt;span style=&quot;font-weight: 400;&quot;&gt;The&amp;nbsp;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;b&gt;X&lt;/b&gt;&lt;span style=&quot;font-weight: 400;&quot;&gt;&amp;nbsp;is projected into:&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/font&gt;&lt;/b&gt;&lt;/li&gt;&lt;ul&gt;&lt;li&gt;&lt;font style=&quot;font-size: 13px;&quot;&gt;&lt;b style=&quot;background-color: transparent; color: light-dark(rgb(0, 0, 0), rgb(255, 255, 255));&quot;&gt;4&amp;nbsp;&lt;/b&gt;&lt;span style=&quot;background-color: transparent; color: light-dark(rgb(0, 0, 0), rgb(255, 255, 255));&quot;&gt;`Q`&amp;nbsp;Linear Layers&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/font&gt;&lt;/li&gt;&lt;li&gt;&lt;font style=&quot;font-size: 13px;&quot;&gt;&lt;b style=&quot;background-color: transparent; color: light-dark(rgb(0, 0, 0), rgb(255, 255, 255));&quot;&gt;1&amp;nbsp;&lt;/b&gt;&lt;span style=&quot;background-color: transparent; color: light-dark(rgb(0, 0, 0), rgb(255, 255, 255));&quot;&gt;`K`&amp;nbsp;Linear layer&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/font&gt;&lt;/li&gt;&lt;li&gt;&lt;font style=&quot;font-size: 13px;&quot;&gt;&lt;b&gt;1&lt;/b&gt;&lt;b style=&quot;background-color: transparent; color: light-dark(rgb(0, 0, 0), rgb(255, 255, 255));&quot;&gt;&amp;nbsp;&lt;/b&gt;&lt;span style=&quot;background-color: transparent; color: light-dark(rgb(0, 0, 0), rgb(255, 255, 255));&quot;&gt;`V`&amp;nbsp;layer&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/font&gt;&lt;/li&gt;&lt;/ul&gt;&lt;li&gt;&lt;font style=&quot;font-size: 13px;&quot;&gt;&lt;span style=&quot;background-color: transparent; color: light-dark(rgb(0, 0, 0), rgb(255, 255, 255));&quot;&gt;There are &lt;/span&gt;&lt;b style=&quot;background-color: transparent; color: light-dark(rgb(0, 0, 0), rgb(255, 255, 255));&quot;&gt;4&lt;/b&gt;&lt;span style=&quot;background-color: transparent; color: light-dark(rgb(0, 0, 0), rgb(255, 255, 255));&quot;&gt; Scaled Dot-Product Attention layers.&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/font&gt;&lt;/li&gt;&lt;/ul&gt;&lt;/div&gt;&lt;div&gt;&lt;font style=&quot;font-size: 13px;&quot;&gt;&lt;font style=&quot;&quot;&gt;&lt;b style=&quot;&quot;&gt;NOTE:&lt;/b&gt; In the Llama 3 8B model there are many more Linear and Scaled Dot-Product layers. I&lt;span style=&quot;color: light-dark(rgb(0, 0, 0), rgb(255, 255, 255)); background-color: transparent;&quot;&gt;t has 32&amp;nbsp;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/font&gt;&lt;span style=&quot;background-color: transparent; color: light-dark(rgb(0, 0, 0), rgb(255, 255, 255));&quot;&gt;`Q`&lt;/span&gt;&lt;font style=&quot;background-color: transparent; color: light-dark(rgb(0, 0, 0), rgb(255, 255, 255));&quot;&gt;&lt;span style=&quot;color: light-dark(rgb(0, 0, 0), rgb(255, 255, 255)); background-color: transparent;&quot;&gt;&amp;nbsp;heads (32 &lt;/span&gt;&lt;/font&gt;&lt;span style=&quot;background-color: transparent; color: light-dark(rgb(0, 0, 0), rgb(255, 255, 255));&quot;&gt;`Q`&amp;nbsp;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;font style=&quot;background-color: transparent; color: light-dark(rgb(0, 0, 0), rgb(255, 255, 255));&quot;&gt;&lt;span style=&quot;color: light-dark(rgb(0, 0, 0), rgb(255, 255, 255)); background-color: transparent;&quot;&gt;Linear stacked layers) and 8&amp;nbsp;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/font&gt;&lt;span style=&quot;background-color: transparent; color: light-dark(rgb(0, 0, 0), rgb(255, 255, 255));&quot;&gt;`K`&lt;/span&gt;&lt;span style=&quot;background-color: transparent; color: light-dark(rgb(0, 0, 0), rgb(255, 255, 255));&quot;&gt;&amp;nbsp;and&amp;nbsp;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;span style=&quot;background-color: transparent; color: light-dark(rgb(0, 0, 0), rgb(255, 255, 255));&quot;&gt;`V`&lt;/span&gt;&lt;span style=&quot;background-color: transparent; color: light-dark(rgb(0, 0, 0), rgb(255, 255, 255));&quot;&gt;&amp;nbsp;heads, which is a `4:1` ratio. `h=32/8=4` This means that a group of `4` `Q` heads will share exactly `1` `K` head and `1` `V` head&lt;/span&gt;&lt;span style=&quot;background-color: transparent; color: light-dark(rgb(0, 0, 0), rgb(255, 255, 255));&quot;&gt;. This group structure is repeated `8` times to account for all `32` `Q`&amp;nbsp; heads.&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/font&gt;&lt;/div&gt;&lt;/div&gt;" vertex="1">
          <mxGeometry height="290" width="360.01" x="20" y="500" as="geometry" />
        </mxCell>
